<h1 id="Search-Algorithms">Search Algorithms<a class="anchor-link" href="#Search-Algorithms">&#182;</a></h1><h2 id="Part-6---A-Star">Part 6 - A Star<a class="anchor-link" href="#Part-6---A-Star">&#182;</a></h2><p>Recall our last solution via UCS. Apart from performing worse than DFS with more iterations, one might also have noticed something else. A cheaper alternative path!</p>

<h3 id="Cost-problem:">Cost problem:<a class="anchor-link" href="#Cost-problem:">&#182;</a></h3><p><strong>Path chosen by UCS</strong>: A - S - F - B =&gt; 138 + 41 + 112 = <font color=red>291</font></p>
<p><strong>Alternate path</strong>: A - S - RV - P - B =&gt; 138 + 49 + 29 + 67 = <font color=blue>283</font></p>
<p>We can make our algorithm to choose a cheaper path, by making better choice of nodes each time we choose one from the <em>bag</em>, the priority queue <code>openSet</code></p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Approach">Approach<a class="anchor-link" href="#Approach">&#182;</a></h2><p>Now we are clear the cost is the determining factor in choosing the next node. If we could add some sense to the gScore, about how we are faring in proceeding <em>towards</em> the goal, that could help to improve the choice. That is,</p>
<p><strong>new_cost = total_cost_from_start_to_that_node + <font color=blue>a value representative of how we are faring towards the goal direction</font></strong></p>
<p>Since its addition, we could think, in terms of same unit, that is, distance itself. In a space, the shortest possible distance between two points, is the straight line distance (SLD) between them. Any path we are going to deduce, will have a cost, always greater to that.</p>
<p>When we are at any node, the shortest <em>virtual</em> straight line distance from that node to goal, could then always help us choose a better node.</p>
<p>Let us call it <strong>heuristic</strong> score hScore or h(n). Let the new cost be fScore or f(n). Then</p>
<p><strong>fScore = gScore + <font color=blue>hScore</font></strong></p>
<p>If there are 3 neighbors to add to the queue, whichever neighbor having least sum of gScore and hScore, that is fScore could be our next best candidate. Why?</p>
<p>Least gScore tells us, that neighbor took least cost to arrive at that point among others.
Least hScore tells us, that neighbor is <em>roughly possibly</em> nearer to the goal than others.</p>
<p>Since we are including only hScore for comparision w.r.t how distant they are from the goal for all nodes, and since that could be the minimum distance possible, we could be sure that, our comparision is fair for all nodes, in our scenario.</p>
<p><strong>Note:</strong></p>
<p>Remember, hScore is kinda approximation. And if costs include more factors, hScore could screw up also. SLD may not always be best hScore in all scenarios. Thus there are multiple ways to calculate hScore. Even SLD approach includes various methods like Euclidean, Manhattan etc. We stick with geodesic SLD for now.</p>
<p>It is also important, <strong>hScore should not over estimate actual cost</strong> as much as possible. Then, we might not be making a fair comparision between the fScores of nodes.</p>
<p>Heuristics is a deep subject by itself, so for now, we will move on with basics. There could never be an end to tuning an algorithm.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h3 id="Algorithm-Development">Algorithm Development<a class="anchor-link" href="#Algorithm-Development">&#182;</a></h3><p>Calculating cost is the primary change now. At every node, calculate a new total cost as below and store that in the queue/bag.</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># f(n) = g(n) + h(n)</span>
<span class="c1"># g(n) = total actual SLD so far from &#39;start&#39; to &#39;current neighbor&#39;</span>
<span class="c1"># h(n) = SLD from current neighbor to &#39;goal&#39;</span>
</pre></div>
<p><strong>gScore</strong></p>
<p>In UCS, we used g(n) as below.</p>
<p>g(n) or gScore of each_neighbor = current_cost from start to current_node + distance(current_node, each_neighbor)</p>
<p>The current_cost was coming directly from queue, because that was what we stored for every node in first place. Now, we are going to store a different cost fScore or f(n) in the queue. So we would need a function to calculate the current_cost value.</p>
<p>We could use <code>cameFrom</code> to track back the nodes till start, and at every iteration, simply calculate the distance and sum up step costs to arrive at gScore. Thus this would be just amalgamation of <code>reconstructPath</code> and <code>distance</code> we already saw.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>

<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">geopy</span>
<span class="kn">from</span> <span class="nn">math</span> <span class="k">import</span> <span class="n">floor</span>

<span class="c1"># TEST SETUP </span>
<span class="n">M</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">romania_location_map</span>
<span class="n">start</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">&#39;A&#39;</span>
<span class="n">cameFrom</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{}</span>           
<span class="n">cameFrom</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">start</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="kc">None</span> 
<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">each_parent</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">M</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">keys</span><span class="p">():</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">each_child</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">M</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">each_parent</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s1">&#39;connections&#39;</span><span class="p">]:</span>
        <span class="n">cameFrom</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">each_child</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">each_parent</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">distance</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">start_node</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">end_node</span><span class="p">):</span>

    <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x0</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">y0</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">M</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">start_node</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s1">&#39;pos&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span>
    <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x1</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">y1</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">M</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">end_node</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s1">&#39;pos&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">floor</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">geopy</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">distance</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">geodesic</span><span class="p">((</span><span class="n">y0</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">x0</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">y1</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">x1</span><span class="p">))</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">miles</span><span class="p">)</span>
        
<span class="c1"># NEEDED FUNCTION TO CALCULATE DISTANCE FROM CURRENT NODE BACK TO START</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">totalDistance</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">current_node</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">cost</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">0</span>
    <span class="k">while</span> <span class="n">current_node</span> <span class="ow">is</span> <span class="ow">not</span> <span class="kc">None</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">parent</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">cameFrom</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">get</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">current_node</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="kc">None</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">parent</span> <span class="ow">is</span> <span class="ow">not</span> <span class="kc">None</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="n">cost</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="n">distance</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">current_node</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">parent</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">current_node</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">parent</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">cost</span> 

<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">totalDistance</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;F&#39;</span><span class="p">))</span>  <span class="c1"># 138 + 41 = 179</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">totalDistance</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;C&#39;</span><span class="p">))</span>  <span class="c1"># 138 + 49 + 29 + 64 = 280</span>

        <span class="n">Path</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">current_node</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="nb">reversed</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Path</span><span class="p">[:</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">])</span>   

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">AStar</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">start</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">goal</span><span class="p">):</span> 

    <span class="c1"># INITIALIZATION</span>
    <span class="n">openSet</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">PriorityQueue</span><span class="p">()</span>
    <span class="n">openSet</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">put</span><span class="p">((</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">start</span><span class="p">))</span>  
    <span class="n">closedSet</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">set</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">start</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">cameFrom</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">start</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="kc">None</span>               
    
    <span class="c1"># MAIN LOOP</span>
    <span class="k">while</span> <span class="ow">not</span> <span class="n">openSet</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">empty</span><span class="p">():</span> 

        <span class="n">current_cost</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">current_node</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">openSet</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">get</span><span class="p">()</span>     

        <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">current_node</span> <span class="ow">is</span> <span class="n">goal</span><span class="p">:</span>   
            <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;Success. Route from </span><span class="si">{}</span><span class="s1"> to </span><span class="si">{}</span><span class="s1"> found. Cost: </span><span class="si">{}</span><span class="s1"> Path: </span><span class="si">{}</span><span class="s1">&#39;</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">format</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">start</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">goal</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">current_cost</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="nb">list</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">reconstructPath</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">current_node</span><span class="p">))))</span>
            <span class="k">break</span>
            
        <span class="c1"># VISUALIZATION PURPOSE</span>
        <span class="n">all_neighbors</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">reversed</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">M</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">get</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">current_node</span><span class="p">,[])</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">get</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;connections&#39;</span><span class="p">,[]))</span>        
        <span class="n">considered_neighbors</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">list</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">set</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">all_neighbors</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="nb">set</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">closedSet</span><span class="p">))</span> <span class="c1"># thank you: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/3462143/get-difference-between-two-lists                   </span>
            
        <span class="n">all_neighbors</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">M</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">get</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">current_node</span><span class="p">,[])</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">get</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;connections&#39;</span><span class="p">,[])</span> 
        <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">each_neighbor</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">all_neighbors</span><span class="p">:</span>      
            <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">each_neighbor</span> <span class="ow">not</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">closedSet</span><span class="p">:</span>  
                
                <span class="c1">#gScore = &#39;cost till current_node&#39; + &#39;cost between current node and its neighbor&#39; </span>
                <span class="n">gScore</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">totalDistance</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">current_node</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">distance</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">current_node</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">each_neighbor</span><span class="p">)</span>
                <span class="n">hScore</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">distance</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">each_neighbor</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">goal</span><span class="p">)</span>
                <span class="n">fScore</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">gScore</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">hScore</span>
                
                <span class="n">openSet</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">put</span><span class="p">((</span><span class="n">fScore</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">each_neighbor</span><span class="p">))</span>                  
                <span class="n">cameFrom</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">each_neighbor</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">current_node</span>    
                <span class="n">closedSet</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">add</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">each_neighbor</span><span class="p">)</span>
                
        <span class="c1"># VISUALIZATION PURPOSE</span>
        <span class="n">_</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">doc</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">computeGraphs</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">current_node</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">considered_neighbors</span><span class="p">)</span>
                
        <span class="c1">#print(openSet.queue)  #just to verify</span>
                
    <span class="c1"># VISUALIZATION PURPOSE</span>
    <span class="n">_</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">doc</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">computeGraphs</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">current_node</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="p">[])</span>            
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="s1">&#39;No Goal found!&#39;</span>
            
            
<span class="n">M</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">romania_location_map</span> 
<span class="n">start</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">&#39;A&#39;</span>
<span class="n">goal</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">&#39;B&#39;</span>

<span class="c1"># VISUALIZATION PURPOSE - called here caz we use doc in ourSearchAlgo</span>
<span class="n">doc</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">Doc</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">M</span><span class="p">)</span> 

<span class="n">result</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">AStar</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">start</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">goal</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># VISUALIZATION PURPOSE</span>
<span class="n">images</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">doc</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">render</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">display</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Image</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">images</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]),</span><span class="n">Image</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">images</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]),</span><span class="n">Image</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">images</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">]))</span>
</pre></div>
